io.neba.api.spi

Interface ResourceModelPostProcessor


  • public interface ResourceModelPostProcessor
    Lifecycle callback for resource models.

    processAfterMapping(Object, Resource, ResourceModelFactory) is invoked after the model was created and injected and all resource properties are mapped. All lifecycle callbacks where already called at this point.

    OSGi services providing this interface are automatically detected by the core and are applied to all resource models. There are no guarantees concerning the order in which these post processors are invoked. If a specific order is required, implementing a ResourceModelPostProcessor that delegates to other post processors in the desired order is advised.
    Since:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Olaf Otto
